JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has dismissed its chief procurement officer Solly Tshitangano with immediate effect following a guilty verdict in his disciplinary process. The utility said that he had been charged with gross misconduct, breach of duties and non-performance. He was suspended in February this year. Eskom said that it relied on evidence of two witnesses and the forensic findings of law firm, Bowmans, with the chairperson of the hearing ruling that there was no choice but to dismiss Tshitangano. #Eskom #MediaStatementEskom dismisses Chief Procurement Officer Solly Tshitangano with immediate effect following a guilty verdict in his disciplinary process@SABCNews@eNCA@ewnupdates @SundayTimesZA @News24 @SowetanLIVE @IOL pic.twitter.com/o4iJNCKAOG  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.